Since there is much more use of `Ico` than `Icc`, this seems to be a useful reformulation.
.. not needed after reminding myself, there is already the same thing with `range`...

I'd be happy to outsource these two lemmas, see my question here: 
https://leanprover.zulipchat.com/#narrow/stream/217875-Is-there-code-for-X.3F/topic/group.20sum.2Fprod.20in.20pairs.20even.20and.20odd.20summands

either here or in a follow-up pull request

Why not just prove (not tested):
```lean
@[to_additive]
lemma Finset.prod_even_odd_range {M : Type*} [CommMonoid M] (n : Nat) (f : Nat ‚Üí M) :
    (‚àè x in range n, f (2 * x)) * (‚àè x in range n, f (2 * x + 1)) = ‚àè x in range (2 * n), f x :=
```
by induction on `n`?

There are many ways to generalize this statement (e.g., from `2` to any number or from `range` to any `Ico` with some divisibility assumptions). I would postpone these generalizations till someone needs them.

I pushed a proof by induction (also, it provides an explicit formula for `n`). If you want to restore helper lemmas from your old proof, then I suggest that you open a new PR with them.
I guess, we need a review from another maintainer now.
maintainer merge
